{"parse":{"title":"Hot potato (game)","pageid":12682501,"revid":860023972,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">This article is about the party game. For the game show, see <a href=\"/wiki/Hot_Potato_(game_show)\" title=\"Hot Potato (game show)\">Hot Potato (game show)</a>. For other uses, see <a href=\"/wiki/Hot_potato_(disambiguation)\" class=\"mw-redirect mw-disambig\" title=\"Hot potato (disambiguation)\">Hot Potato</a>.</div>\n<p><b>Hot potato</b> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Party_game\" title=\"Party game\">party game</a> that involves players gathering in a <a href=\"/wiki/Circle\" title=\"Circle\">circle</a> and tossing a small object such as a <a href=\"/wiki/Beanbag\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Beanbag\">beanbag</a> or even a real potato to each other while music plays.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The player who is holding the object when the music stops is eliminated.<sup id=\"cite_ref-rules_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-rules-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Origins\">Origins</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Hot_potato_(game)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Origins\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The origins of the hot potato game are not clear. However, it may go back as far as 1888 when <a href=\"/wiki/Sidney_Oldall_Addy\" title=\"Sidney Oldall Addy\">Sidney Oldall Addy</a>'s <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Glossary_of_Sheffield_Words&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Glossary of Sheffield Words (page does not exist)\">Glossary of Sheffield Words</a> describes a game in which a number of people sit in a row, or in chairs round a <a href=\"/wiki/Parlor\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Parlor\">parlor</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-glossary_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-glossary-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> In this game, a lighted <a href=\"/wiki/Candle\" title=\"Candle\">candle</a> is handed to the first person, who says:\n</p>\n<style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r856303468\">.mw-parser-output .templatequote{overflow:hidden;margin:1em 0;padding:0 40px}.mw-parser-output .templatequote .templatequotecite{line-height:1.5em;text-align:left;padding-left:1.6em;margin-top:0}</style><blockquote class=\"templatequote\"><div class=\"poem\">\n<p>Jack's alive, and likely to live<br />\nIf he dies in your hand, you've a forfeit to give.\n</p>\n</div>\n</blockquote>\n<p>The one in whose hand the light expires has to pay the forfeit.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Hot_potato_(game)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Bagholder\" title=\"Bagholder\">Bagholder</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Musical_chairs\" title=\"Musical chairs\">Musical chairs</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Pass_the_parcel\" title=\"Pass the parcel\">Pass the parcel</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Passing_the_buck\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Passing the buck\">Passing the buck</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Hot_potato_(game)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Wise, Derba (2003-11-10). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=wTuZMWvmUisC\"><i>Great Big Book of Children's Games</i></a>. McGraw Hill Professional. p.&#160;266. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780071422468\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780071422468\">9780071422468</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Great+Big+Book+of+Children%27s+Games&amp;rft.pages=266&amp;rft.pub=McGraw+Hill+Professional&amp;rft.date=2003-11-10&amp;rft.isbn=9780071422468&amp;rft.aulast=Wise&amp;rft.aufirst=Derba&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.co.uk%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DwTuZMWvmUisC&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHot+potato+%28game%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-rules-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-rules_2-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Maguire, Jack (1990). <i>Hopscotch, Hangman, Hot Potato &amp; Ha Ha Ha: A Rulebook of Children's Games</i>. New York: Simon and Schuster. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0671763326\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0671763326\">0671763326</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Hopscotch%2C+Hangman%2C+Hot+Potato+%26+Ha+Ha+Ha%3A+A+Rulebook+of+Children%27s+Games&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Simon+and+Schuster&amp;rft.date=1990&amp;rft.isbn=0671763326&amp;rft.aulast=Maguire&amp;rft.aufirst=Jack&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHot+potato+%28game%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"displa